North Korea says that the "never" will disarm unilaterally without confidence
The Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs of North Korea told the United Nations last Saturday that continued sanctions deepened their mistrust towards the United States and it was not possible that the country would surrender its nuclear weapons unilaterally under such circumstances.
Ri Yong Ho told the World Organisation's annual General Assembly that in recent years North Korea had taken "meaning measures to show its goodwill", for example by stopping nuclear and missile tests, dismantling the installations for nuclear tests and promising not to spread nuclear weapons and nuclear technology.
